&lt;p&gt;Are you good with computers, organised and have administrative experience?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an administrator to join our Tactical Operations centre on a permanent part-time basis at Chelmsford offices. Flexible hours are welcome to be discussed. There will be a potential for a requirement to support with weekend working in the future on a rotational basis which would attract additional payments inline with the Agenda for change - Section 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve working independatly but also as a part of a wider team and closely with Tactical Operations Centre management team to support the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Microsoft Office skills are essential, as is the ability to be discreet and maintain confidentiality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst the role will primarily be based at Broomfield, Chelmsford, it is potential for the successful candidate to be able to work elsewhere as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keiran Bromley, Duty Tactical Commander&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;keiran.bromley@eastamb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
